fields.physical_description:
1.  tray, rectangular board with an edge on all sides; painted dark gloss blue
2,3.  archway with corner pillars, the arch is painted gloss red
At each corner is a pillar painted gloss grey.   The pillars taper to a point.
         Ht. 4¾in x 3 5/8in x 2¾in (12 x 9.2 x 7cm)
4,5.  staircase, cut to show four steps; painted gloss red
         Ht. 2¼in x 1¾in x L.3¼in (5.7 x 4.5 x 8.3cm)
6-9.  stair sides, sloped top painted gloss red with a pillar at the short end; pillars match those on the archways
         Ht. 3½in x 3 3/8in x ½in (8.9 x 8.6 x 1.2cm)
10-13.  hedges, double rounded top edge with a pillar at one end; one side painted gloss dark blue, the other gloss green with the pillars red
         Ht. 4½ x 6in x ½in (11.4 x 15.3 x 1.2cm)
14-25.  grass or reeds, 12, painted dark gloss green.  Each piece is cut with a double toothed edge at the top.  Each point is cut slightly to the right side.
         Ht. 1¾in x 3 5/8in x ½in (4.5 x 9.2 x 1.2cm)
*26-37.  bank sides; 12 panels in two colours of gloss green (one light and the other dark) and in 3 different sizes and shapes.  All have one straight side painted tan brown.  The shapes are basically triangular with one side slightly wavy.
26,27.  light green, narrow at top edge,  Ht. 3 3/8in x 1¾in (8.6 x 4.5cm)
28,29.  dark green, as 26,27
30,31.  light green, 1in width at top edge, Ht. 3 3/8in (8.6cm)
32,33.  dark green, as 30,31
34,35.  light green, broad at top edge.  Ht. 3 3/8in (8.6cm)
36,37.  dark green, as 34,35
38-41.  furrows, painted mid brown gloss; straight with wavy top edge
             L. 6¾in (17.2cm) x w. ¼in
42-45.  furrows, painted mid brown and yellow gloss; two sides have wavy edges
             L. 7¼in x gt. w.1in (18.4 x 2.5cm)
*46-57.   sea waves, painted mid blue gloss with the top edge a lighter blue.  In all cases, the top edges are wavy.
46,47.  wavy on two sides.   18.5 x 2.5 x 1.9cm
48,49.  wavy on two sides.   18.5 x 2 x 1.9cm
50,51.  double wave on top.  18.5 x 2.5 x  1.2cm
52,53.  single wave on top    18.5 x 1.9 x 1.2cm
54,55.  single wave on top    15 x 1.9 x 1.2cm
56,57.  single wave on top    15 x 2.5 x 1.2cm
fields.title: riverbank
fields.materials_techniques: wood, painted with gloss paint in primary colours
fields.location: Museum of Childhood, Creativity Gallery, case 11
fields.marks:
signed lower left edge of tray in light blue paint:-  T& C VINCENT 1984
title lower right edge in light blue paint:-  RIVERBANK
fields.history_note:
References: A wooden craft toy designed and made by Ted Vincent who was on the Crafts Council register of Toy Makers but not a member of the Toy Makers Guild.  It is an imaginative and original constructional puzzle toy.  

Purchased by the donor from Hitchcock's, 10 Chapel Row, Bath, BA1 1HN, for the sum of £138.70 on April 30, 1990 (received May 2, 1990).
It was been donated in memory of Rosamund Wight, died September 1989, and Elizabeth Murdoch, died April 1991, both past member of staff at Bethnal Green Museum of Childhood.
